criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Male and female patients ≥ 18 years old

          2. Patients willing to participate in the investigation and signing the Patient Informed
             Consent (PIC) Form;

          3. Indication to CRT-D implant according to current ESC Guidelines on cardiac pacing and
             cardiac resynchronization therapy

          4. Sinus rhythm at time of implant;

          5. Optimized medical therapy according to current ESC Guidelines

          6. Rest heart rate (HR) >45 bpm at baseline ECG, with betablocker therapy at optimal
             medical dosage; or, if rest HR<45 bpm: maximum heart rate at the 6- minute walking
             test >85 bpm.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Any indication to atrial pacing according to current guidelines;

          2. Both: resting heart rate <45 bpm at baseline ECG, with betablocker therapy at optimal
             medical dosage and maximum heart rate at the 6-minute walking test <85 bpm;

          3. NYHA Class IV;

          4. Permanent Atrial Fibrillation

          5. Replacement of/upgrading from previously implanted pacing system;

          6. Dialysis patients;

          7. Pregnant or breast-feeding women.
